From 8afc24ab5dea724276bb6ec610bfc1d59d2f1934 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Nadia Chambers <nadia.yvette.chambers@ik.me>
Date: Sat, 2 May 2026 06:13:25 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 086/174] mm/memory: drop do_anonymous_page +(rss-1) _mapcount
 compensation
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The PGCL fault-around path in do_anonymous_page() previously did:

    folio_add_new_anon_rmap(folio, vma, addr, RMAP_EXCLUSIVE);
    /* sets _mapcount = 0 (= 1 mapping) */
    if (rss > 1) {
        folio_ref_add(folio, rss - 1);
        atomic_add(rss - 1, &folio->_mapcount);  /* <-- this */
    }

The +(rss-1) atomic_add was a compensation hack: do_anonymous_page
installs PAGE_MMUCOUNT sub-page PTEs in one shot, but the per-PTE
walker (page_vma_mapped_walk) then yielded once per PTE, calling
folio_remove_rmap_*() per yield.  To balance the per-PTE
decrements, fault time padded _mapcount up by (rss-1) so the final
count would land at -1 ("fully unmapped") after PAGE_MMUCOUNT
single-PTE walker iterations.

Now that the walker yields one kernel page per step (commit
3b5f425f0197) and try_to_unmap_one decrements _mapcount once per
yield (commit ff154fa36c21), the natural accounting is:

  fault   : folio_add_new_anon_rmap        →  _mapcount = 0  (1 mapping)
  unmap   : 1 walker yield × 1 dec         →  _mapcount = -1 (0 mappings)

No compensation required.  Under PGCL the kernel page is mapped
ONCE from this VMA — the fact that PAGE_MMUCOUNT sub-page PTEs back
the same kernel page is a hardware-page-table artifact, not
multiple distinct mappings.  Refcount and RSS remain MMUPAGE-
granular (one per PTE).

PGCL=4 + THP={on,off} regression-tested clean post-change: cow.c
PASS, zero BUG/Oops events.  PGCL=0/2 pre-existing rss-counter
classification BUGs (folio identity flip mid-life; see
project_aarch64_pgcl0_rss.md) remain — they are unrelated to this
walker semantics work and require separate investigation.

Signed-off-by: Nadia Chambers <nadia.yvette.chambers@gmail.com>
---
 mm/memory.c | 26 ++++++++++++++------------
 1 file changed, 14 insertions(+), 12 deletions(-)

diff --git a/mm/memory.c b/mm/memory.c
index 290ce662e5ee..ed81cd52088a 100644
--- a/mm/memory.c
+++ b/mm/memory.c
@@ -5907,20 +5907,22 @@ static vm_fault_t do_anonymous_page(struct vm_fault *vmf)
 			rss++;
 		}
 		/*
-		 * Adjust refcount and rmap for the extra PTEs.
-		 * folio_add_new_anon_rmap set mapcount to 0 (= 1 mapping)
-		 * and PageAnonExclusive.  Add rmap for the extras.
+		 * Adjust refcount for the extra PTEs created by fault-around.
+		 * folio_add_new_anon_rmap already set _mapcount = 0 (= 1
+		 * mapping = 1 kernel page) which is correct under PGCL: even
+		 * though we just installed PAGE_MMUCOUNT sub-page PTEs, they
+		 * collectively represent ONE mapping of this kernel page from
+		 * this VMA.  The walker (page_vma_mapped_walk) yields once
+		 * per kernel page, and try_to_unmap_one decrements _mapcount
+		 * once per yield; the previous +(rss-1) compensation that
+		 * matched a per-PTE walker is no longer needed.
+		 *
+		 * Refcount remains MMUPAGE-granular (one per PTE) since each
+		 * PTE-level operation in the unmap path takes one reference.
+		 * RSS counter is also MMUPAGE-granular.
 		 */
-		if (rss > 1) {
+		if (rss > 1)
 			folio_ref_add(folio, rss - 1);
-			/*
-			 * For a newly allocated exclusive folio, all sub-page
-			 * PTEs map the same folio.  Use atomic_add on _mapcount
-			 * directly since folio_add_new_anon_rmap already set
-			 * up the anon_vma and the folio is exclusively owned.
-			 */
-			atomic_add(rss - 1, &folio->_mapcount);
-		}
 		/* Fix RSS: we added 1 above (nr_pages), need rss total */
 		add_mm_counter(vma->vm_mm, MM_ANONPAGES, rss - 1);
 		update_mmu_cache_range(vmf, vma, addr, vmf->pte, 1);
-- 
